<seg id="1">Climate adversity has slowed the economy</seg>
</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">During the first year of management of Mario Lopez Valdez, Sinaloa unemployment and informality increased foreign investment has fallen and the economy shrank</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3">2011 is a year in which he will be remembered in the economic history of Sinaloa, this is the first year of Government of Mario Lopez Valdez, auto-appelé of change, which has generated great expectations regarding the advances of the economy, but given the climate adversity at the beginning of the year, the increase was not observed, there is a deterioration of the main indicators of economic development.</seg>
<seg id="4">The temperatures in February, besides causing loss of trillions to the agricultural sector, have limited the ability of the economy to growth, have caused a contraction in economic activity in general by 3.6 percent in the first half of the year, supported mainly by the historic decline of 31.16 percent in agriculture, which has affected the dynamics of other economic sectors.</seg>
<seg id="5">According to the report of assignments by the frozen out by the Mexican Council of Rural Development Soutenable, there has been damage to 582 million 835 hectares, including a 78,03 percent suffered damage and the rest of 21.07, percent suffered partial damage, the main crops affected were vegetables, corn and chick peas.</seg>
<seg id="6">The economic downturn has generated, until November, a steady rise in unemployment in the state, according to the National Institute of Statistics and Geography the unemployment rate in the state during the first three quarters of the year there has been a rapid increase, because during the January to March 55 000 053 sinaloens were unemployed, with a rate of 4.53 percent Population Economics Active, in the second quarter the rate became 5.28 percent and from July to September, the average has continued to raise up to 6.19 percent, a rate that represents more than 74 thousand sinaloens unemployed, an increase compared to the first half of 18,000 969 people.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7">Less liquidity of</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8">Unemployment in Sinaloa during the year is multifactorial, according to the economist Gerardo Lopez Cervantes, director of the Faculty of Sciences Economiques et Sociales of the UAS, rising unemployment can be explained by the actions carried out by public policy.</seg>
<seg id="9">"What we are seeing is an increase in unemployment, which is due to various factors, among which the loss of liquidity in the market due to a restriction of resources by the approved legislation in Congress to combat money laundering, because for people who earn dollars in an illicit manner, it is not easy work for the win, they invest them and use them in something," he says.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="10">Migration detained</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="11">Lopez Cervantes said that rising unemployment is also due to a demographic factor.</seg>
<seg id="12">"The number of people leaving the state to go to work abroad, the United States has been restricted, first because of the difficulties of entry and secondly because entering they have already struggling to find work, these people to stay here and there are sources of work, which means that unemployment rise," déclaré-t-il.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="13">Lack of serious</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="14">The analysis of the labour market sinaloen worsens in considering the high level of lack of seriousness that predominates among the working conditions, according to INEGI, the 60,38 percent of the working population in this state is working without pay as worker in any social insurance institution.</seg>
<seg id="15">Apart from unemployment and the lack of seriousness, another reason to shift to the state are low wages, the entity has the lowest wages in the country, according to the records of the Mexican Institute for Social Insurance and the Ministry of Labour and Social Forecasting.</seg>
<seg id="16">The average monthly income of workers sinaloens was, until September, 5 000 352 pesos, well below the national average of 7 thousand 375 pesos.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="17">Contraction of FDI</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="18">As part of the decline in economic activity and rising unemployment, in 2011 recorded the largest reduction of Foreign Direct Investment in the past 10 years, according to the Ministry of Economy from January to June the State FDI reached 630 thousand 697 million, representing a decrease of 87.74% compared to 143 000 312 $5 million registered in the same period of the previous year.</seg>
<seg id="19">In turn, the Secretariat of Economic Development of the State Government has a total investment of $17,280 trillion pesos per year, mainly by companies in the service sector.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="20">The debt</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="21">Given the scenario of economic contraction, the State Government has asked Congress in July in public approval of a credit of 3 trillion pesos, for investment in infrastructure projects in the 18 municipes, with the aim of reactivating the economy, congressional approval of the State was 2,600 trillion pesos and until November there was no benefit of debt in any sector of the economy of the state.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="22">Reactions to</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="23">The representatives of the business sector, the first year of Government of Mario López Valdés demonstrates a lack of management capacity of the Government.</seg>
<seg id="24">Miguel Loredo López, president of the National Chamber of the Transformation Industry, said that in 2011 there has not been a harmonization of the wishes of the various sectors, including the State Government.</seg>
<seg id="25">"The performance of the economy of Sinaloa during this year has been really very poor, we must work hard to regain the ground we lost this year in 2012 we must double our effort, it was necessary to align the efforts of everyone, especially the already synchronized this new team of Government, hope that next year will be much better," he said.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="26">Economic slow pace</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="27">Loredo López said that events such as the frozen at the beginning of the year have retained the economy of the state and have restricted his performance and growth.</seg>
<seg id="28">"The low economic fluxe is a product of several events, among which jellies, one of the main effect has been a slow economy that is fast enough to generate economic dynamism that makes it possible to have an acceptable level he flow in the trial, products and services, and therefore, at the end of the year we are far below the expectations that we had," he says.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="29">Redefine the importantnot</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="30">For Teodoro Salazar Uriarte, president of the Confederation for Mexican Sinaloa has said that it wants to harness the State towards productive activities more dynamism.</seg>
<seg id="31">"In general terms, we found that it worked, we believe that it is necessary to develop a long-term programme which redefined the role and the economic direction of the state, because it is important that detonates the full potential of material and human resources of Sinaloa," he says.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="32">Much to do</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="33">The president of the Coparmex stressed the importance of establishing a vision of the future that channels better government efforts.</seg>
<seg id="34">"In general terms, I would say that the Government has made efforts to give good results in various fields, in terms of economic development there is some progress, but it is important to develop a euro in the long term," he said.</seg>
<seg id="35">He noted that the current administration has shown advances in the way of public policy management.</seg>
<seg id="36">"There are elements which enable us to say that the Government is more inclusive, what I can say is that it was a lot of work and the Government is aware of the fact that there is still much to be done," he says.</seg>
</p>
