</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">According to the data highlighted by PERs, the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes for 879 6 thousand 74 minutes total.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3">The possibility of the count "vote by vote" is a reality in regard to the electoral process this year in Michoacán, where according to data highlighted by the preliminary election results (PER) the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes for 879 6 thousand 74 minutes total.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="4">In this sense, the president of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (EMI), Maria de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, the past 9 November, the electoral body approved a set of guidelines to harmonize local standards to the federal electoral reform.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5">It will be recalled that Michoacán has not approved or its Political Constitution and the Electoral Code of State or the Electoral Act, Justice, at the same time that the state Congress approved reforms that will shortly before the legal deadline for the electoral process can enter into force and the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel failed its publication in the deadlines specified by the Act of the Official Journal of the state, with the argument that he had some objections.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="6">The same 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the (SCJN) has solved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local Legislative Authority and described as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the representative of the state for constitutional reform, because he did not have the right to "sanction or challenge."</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7">Interviewed on the possibility of "vote by vote," Maria de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the guidelines by the General Council of which it will be possible to achieve the total and partial counts the votes by the local electoral body.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="8">Thus, the counting of votes, one or more electoral packages, it may be that: The results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no record of voting and counting in the case of the ballot box is not among the president; or there are errors or obvious alterations of minutes.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="9">In addition, the total count of votes received in all the ballot boxes from the election can be achieved when there is an indication of the fact that the difference between the candidate presumed winner of the election and had the second place in the poll is equal to or less than a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session is a petition from the representative of the party or coalition that made the second of the candidates reported.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="10">The total amount of voting can also be achieved if at the end of the joint statement, it follows that the difference between the candidate and the presumed winner of the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is a petition from the representative of the political party whose candidate came second, in which case we will exclude the electoral packets that have been subject of partial count.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="11">It should be noted that this is the situation of the election of Morelia, where according to the PPRD, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of 923 total minutes.</seg>
</p>
